In a Cabinet meeting on June 21, 2018, President Trump discussed a range of topics, including immigration, employment claims, trade deals, and North Korea. He expressed frustration with Democrats for not approving immigration solutions and accused them of causing damage and suffering. He also highlighted the need for Congress to close loopholes in immigration laws and called for a merit-based immigration system. President Trump praised his administration's efforts on trade deals and the economy, as well as the progress made with North Korea. Additionally, he discussed plans to reorganize government agencies to improve efficiency and address issues such as food safety and job training. The President emphasized the need for lawmakers to come together and work on immigration reform, but also noted the challenges of getting bipartisan support.